cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD) as it applies a DNN-HMM hybrid speech recognizer to TED Talks speech data. It could also belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL) as it deals with speech recognition. Additionally, it could belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as it involves training a DNN with regularizers to select important nodes for achieving high classification power.
